@startuml
title Client Rejects Order

participant "master/mqtt.py" as MasterMqtt
queue "MQTT Broker" as Broker
participant "client/mqtt.py" as ClientMqtt
participant "client/orders.py" as ClientOrders
participant "client/state.py" as ClientState
participant "master/master.py" as Master

MasterMqtt -> Broker : publish invalid order
Broker --> ClientMqtt : order
ClientMqtt -> ClientOrders : accept_or_reject(order)
ClientOrders --> ClientMqtt : rejected(reason)
ClientMqtt -> ClientState : add_error(orderError)
ClientMqtt -> ClientState : mark_dirty("order rejected")
ClientMqtt -> Broker : publish state with error

Broker --> Master : state with error

note right of ClientOrders
  V0 rejection reasons:
  - wrong orderUpdateId
  - already executing another order
  - invalid node/edge sequence
  - first node not reachable
end note
@enduml
